A table has start_date and end_date columns â€” how would you calculate the total number of overlapping days across all rows?


SELECT 
    SUM(
        DATEDIFF(
            LEAST(a.end_date, b.end_date),
            GREATEST(a.start_date, b.start_date)
        ) + 1
    ) AS total_overlap_days
FROM events a
JOIN events b 
  ON a.id < b.id  -- avoid self-join duplicates
 AND a.start_date <= b.end_date
 AND b.start_date <= a.end_date;

