SELF JOIN Applications: ï‚§ Discussed scenarios like finding manager-employee relationships within the same table

A SELF JOIN is when a table is joined to itself â€”
you treat the same table as two different tables using aliases.
This is useful when rows within the same table are related to each other â€” for example:

SELECT 
    e.emp_name AS employee,
    m.emp_name AS manager
FROM employees e
LEFT JOIN employees m
ON e.manager_id = m.emp_id;


